==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''mittitac'', compound of ''mitti-'' (see [[Mitte]]) and ''-tac'' (see [[Tag]]).  Originally *''middidag'', compare Dutch [[middag]]
===Noun===
'''Mittag''' ''m'' (plural [[Mittage]])

# [[noon]], [[midday]].

